<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,367,393]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[406,414,386,400]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">1</subScript>
with brown setae at the base. Fore and mid legs light brown, tarsus dark brown with black macrosetae. Hind femur longer that tibia with thin, long, white setae ventrally; hind tibia with dense, thin, long, brown setae dorsally, ventrally on basal half with dense, thin, long, brown setae, and white on apical half; tarsus with black macrosetae. Abdominal tergites I and II with white setae, remaining tergites with short, sparse, dark setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" box="[199,1073,511,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[427,532,511,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">holotype</typeStatus>
). Total body length 
<quantity box="[754,836,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="22.0">22 mm</quantity>
; wing length 
<quantity box="[987,1069,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Head</emphasis>
: light-brown. Scape light brown basally; remaining antennal segments missing. Ocellar triangle of same color of head. Gena with light-yellow setae; facial gibbosity developed on ventral half, face only with yellow macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[246,336,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Visible maxillary palpus yellow. Proboscis black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[919,1017,619,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Thorax:</emphasis>
brown. Postpronotum in dorsal view with long, light-yellow setae, some black macrosetae at margins; mesonotum laterally with four brown areas, and one large medial elongate reddish-brown area, with short black setae dorsally, and apically with long white setae; scutellum with long, light-yellow setae (
<figureCitation box="[599,688,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Pleurites paler than mesonotum, and with long, light-yellow setae (
<figureCitation box="[160,249,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Fore and mid legs light-brown, coxae with long, light-yellow setae; femora with light-yellow setae basally and black macrosetae distributed over entire surface; tibia with short reddish setae and black setae over entire surface; tarsi with macrosetae and thick black setae that give an overall black coloration. Hind leg light brown; coxa with long light-yellow setae; femur longer than tibia, with white setae ventrally, glabrous dorsally; tibia ventrally with brown setae on basal half, apical half with white setae; dorsally with brown setae, increasing in size from base to apex. First tarsomere (other segments missing) with short black setae dorsally, ventrally with short yellow setae, black macrosetae on the entire surface (
<figureCitation box="[596,687,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Wings coloration opaque yellow, with strong brown setae at base of C vein, present up to humeral crossvein; vein R1 with brown setae at base. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1018,1135,1015,1041]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Abdomen</emphasis>
: brown. T1–2 light-yellow setae dorsally, T3–8 short black setae dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[696,788,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); ventrally light-yellow setae homogeneously distributed (
<figureCitation box="[160,248,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[175,1413,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Mallophora kalos sp. nov. A) Habitus, dorsal view; B) habitus, lateral view; C) face, anterior view; D) male hind leg, anterior view. Total body length 22 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529457" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529457/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
). Epandria short and brown, with white setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" box="[199,411,1123,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1123,1149]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Female</emphasis>
: Unknown
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new species takes the name from the Greek καλός, beautiful, given the attractive color pattern of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1231,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Distribution.</emphasis>
This new species is known from a single locality in the Oriental plains, Los Llanos, which are tropical savannas in the Department of 
<collectingRegion box="[590,671,1267,1293]" country="Colombia" name="Arauca" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Arauca</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[685,747,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1435,181,1123]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Map of northern South America with distribution of Mallophora gauteovan sp. nov. and Mallophora kalos sp. nov. in Colombia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4529459" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4529459/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Fig 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="435" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1303,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[324,525,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,525,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[533,624,1303,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[533,624,1303,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[964,1098,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[964,1098,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the brown body color, the distribution of setae on the hind tibia, in which the basal half ventrally has brown setae and the apical half are white; the predominance of white setae all over the body; and the long hind tibia. 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[977,1176,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[977,1176,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1182,1271,1375,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1182,1271,1375,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
will key out to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[151,305,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[151,305,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using the key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A." box="[495,777,1411,1437]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" pagination="5 - 182" refId="ref4583" refString="Artigas, J. &amp; Angulo, A. (1980) Revision del genero Mallophora Macquart por sistematica alfa y taxonomia numerica (Diptera - Asilidae). Revista Gayana Zoologia, 43 (5), 5 - 182. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / part / 65775  / summary]" type="journal article" year="1980">Artigas &amp; Angulo (1980)</bibRefCitation>
because of the distribution of the setae on the hind tibia, in which they increase in length toward the basal third, and by the presence of white setae on the hind femur. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[207,362,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[207,362,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a black body, the abdomen has yellow setae on all tergites, has hyaline wings, and the male genitalia have white setae, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[548,747,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[548,747,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[753,842,1519,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[753,842,1519,1545]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a brown body, the setae are predominantly white, the wings are opaque, and the male genitalia does not have white setae. Some of these color differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,351,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,351,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[357,447,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[357,447,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[501,655,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[501,655,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be because the 
<typeStatus box="[902,1000,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[1037,1237,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1037,1237,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1243,1333,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1333,1591,1617]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seems to have been collected in ethanol and then pinned dry. If so, some change in coloration might have occurred. Nonetheless, even if some fading occurred, the color pattern of the hind tibia is very different to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Artigas &amp; Angulo" authorityYear="1980" box="[1194,1348,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thompsoni">
<emphasis box="[1194,1348,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. thompsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, clearly pointing that the two are different species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,400,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,400,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[407,498,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[407,498,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[704,859,1736,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[704,859,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[866,956,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[866,956,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" box="[1015,1170,1736,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gauteovan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1015,1170,1736,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">M. gauteovan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1177,1267,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1177,1267,1735,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is more robust and darker, it has yellow setae on abdominal tergites 2–8, the face shows a clear brown spot between the antennae and the proboscis, the face has yellow and black macrosetae, and it lacks setae on the vein R1. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Yepes &amp; Forero, 2021" authorityName="Yepes &amp; Forero" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Mallophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kalos" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">Mallophora kalos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[311,399,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[311,399,1843,1869]" pageId="4" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, can be differentiated by the predominantly yellow color of the setae, and the tarsomeres only with black setae, suggesting that they are different species.
</paragraph>
